    {
      "id": "2adc3fb63f8593ad402624b3134b370f3fc0e2b6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-07 21:15:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nGood point from Oleg, I'm removing my approval.  I was trying to remember why we allowed this, but I couldn't think why it was useful from a \"$PWD/{filename}\" usage.  It definitely makes sense if the full pathname is specified.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6cd48fb2f746031ce795767ccd3a5ae06cb2b196",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 137,
        "name": "Richard Henwood",
        "email": "richard.henwood@intel.com",
        "username": "rhenwood",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-12-07 22:04:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks for this feedback. I am unclear why it is necessary to support'lctl {get|set}_param <path>'. The manual is also unclear [1].\n\nWhat I would like to know is: \n - does 'lctl {get|set}_param' need to support arbitrary paths? in which case this change will be abandoned...\n\n - or I should add the restriction to paths starting with proc that Oleg suggested.\n\n\n36.3.3. Setting Parameters with lctl \n\n\n1. just down from:\nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual-reviews/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.html#dbdoclet.50438219_76969",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3ceee8fe59db5f81c3425628dd422bae04bb00e5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-08 00:18:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think Oleg's proposal to limit paths to start with /proc is reasonable.  The intent is only to check and set Lustre parameters with this tool, so if it isn't a simple tunable (that is put under /proc internally) or a path starting with /proc then it shouldn't work.\n\nIf we ever move the /proc tunables/stats somewhere else (e.g. /sys) then this could be handled internally to lctl.\n\nPeople shouldn't be using absolute pathnames anyway, so I wouldn't object to printing a warning on stderr for any absolute pathnames starting with /proc that this usage is deprecated.  Internally, adding a check like:\n\n#if LUSTRE_VERSION_CODE >= OBD_OCD_VERSION(2,6,50,0)\n#warning \"remove deprecated full path tunable access\"\n#endif\n\nwould ensure that this usage has a limited lifespan.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2e503745bf12d2aa063efe874645ef6acc7f2101",
      "author": {
